The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Monday, November 11, 2002  Good Morning Hello It's Monday, November 11, 2002				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	Southern Avenue. Work is in progress on the drainage pumping station.				 																																	Chowringhee Road. A flyover is coming up.				 																Cinema				 																																	The International Forum of New Cinema, a part of the 8th Kolkata Film Festival, will be inaugurated by Suchitra Mitra at Hind cinema, 6 pm. Mrinal Sen will be present. A screening of Hemanter Pakhi will follow. 				 																Folk music				 																																	Abbas Mela, organised by Abbasuddin Smaran Samity, will be inaugurated on the Maidan at 5 pm. Mayor Subrata Mukherjee and ministers Subhas Chakraborty and Asok Bhattacharya will attend.				 																Fabrics				 																																	Khadi  The Fabric of Freedom, an exhibition of khadi fabrics sponsored by the Volkart Foundation, Switzerland, at Academy of Fine Arts, from 12 noon.				 																Lecture				 																																	Prof J.V. Narlikar, director of Inter-University Consortium for Astronomy and Astrophysics, will deliver the 13th S.N. Bose Memorial Lecture on Facts and Speculations in Cosmology at S.N. Bose National Centre for Basic Sciences, 3 pm.				 																Career fair				 																																	10th Career Fair at Ice Skating Rink from 10 am.				 																Workshop				 																																	A workshop conducted by Firenza Guidi of European Live Arts Network on the performing arts at Seagull Arts and Media Resource Centre, 2 pm-7 pm.
